0:44:2517.name: jaro
0:44:2517.docs:
Calculates the Jaro similarity between two strings. The returned value
is between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher value means more similar).

```
use strsim::jaro;

assert!((0.392 - jaro("Friedrich Nietzsche", "Jean-Paul Sartre")).abs() <
        0.001);
```
